Package smarthome.domain.actuator

Class ActuatorOfLimiter

java.lang.Object
smarthome.domain.actuator.ActuatorOfLimiter
All Implemented Interfaces:
AggregateRoot<ActuatorId>, DomainEntity<ActuatorId>, Actuator
public class ActuatorOfLimiter extends Object implements Actuator
This class represents an actuator with a lower and upper limit. The actuator operates within these limits and is identified by a unique ActuatorId.

      actuatorModelName - the model name of the actuator

    • ActuatorOfLimiter

      protected ActuatorOfLimiter (ActuatorId actuatorId, IntLimit lowerLimit, IntLimit upperLimit, ActuatorModelName actuatorModelName, DeviceId deviceId)
      Constructs an ActuatorOfLimiter with the specified actuator id, lower limit, upper limit, model name, and device id. If the actuator id is null, a new actuator id is generated.
      Parameters:
      actuatorId - the actuator id of this actuator. If null, a new actuator id is generated.
      lowerLimit - the lower limit of the actuator
      upperLimit - the upper limit of the actuator
      actuatorModelName - the model name of the actuator
      deviceId - the device id of the actuator
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any of the parameters are null or if the lower limit is not less than the upper limit

    • operate

      public Value operate (Value value) throws NumberFormatException
      Operates the actuator within the specified value. If the value is within the lower and upper limits, the value is returned. If the value is outside the limits, null is returned.
      Parameters:
      value - the value to operate within
      Returns:
      the value if it is within the limits, null otherwise
      Throws:
      NumberFormatException - if the value cannot be parsed to an integer
